label: F-Pnm Français 1585 (Machaut B)

metadata.label: Repository
metadata.value: Bibliothèque nationale de France, Département des Manuscrits

description:
Copy of the [US-NYw (Vogüé manuscript)][1] of the 14th century, though its script and notation are rougher. Produced by nine text scribes and two music scribes (one scribal hand may have been responsible for corrections).There is no leaf in Pn 1585 corresponding to the empty page f. 138 in US-NYw, while the lost folio US-NYw f. 321 is placed erroneously in Pn 1585 as f. 309. In addition, the first folio of the lays and the next-to-the-last folio of the Virelais is missing in Pn 1585. The inventory of Pn 1585 corresponds with that of US-NYw, but the two missing Rondeaux in US-NYw are here numbered Pn 1585 83A and 83B.


  [1]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/sources/3774/
